"I also do not believe that, if this were to be done, the independence of the regulatory body would be affected." She also recalled that the central government is responsible for planning strategic policy areas, such as the telecommunications sector, for constitutional reasons, because it is responsible for public affairs.
The replacement of analogue signals by digital is one of the most important changes that have taken place around the world in recent years, and it will make better use of the radio-electric spectrum, increased quality of the signal and more channels.
