These matters, they stressed, "made the action of the entire system necessary, in accordance with the principle of economic governance by the State, they included a group of features that put the Constitution in the hands of the central government."
It recalled that many countries around the world had already implemented the digital transition, including the government, although they had highly specialised institutions.
It could not be concluded that the government would intervene in the powers of the Congress with the issue of the contested legislative decree, because the laws adopted by the legislature would be respected, "she assured.
