The Prime Minister, Mario Monti, will meet with the President of Italy tomorrow to present to him the new government which is to face the crisis that has led Italy to the brink of economic collapse.
A communication from the Presidential Palace announced that the Monti appointed on Sunday would meet with the President of the Republic, Giorgio Napolitano, on Wednesday to confirm government formation.
