Occupied house in which huge parties were held was cleared
The house owners had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments in the building on the street Balmes no. 51 (Barcelona).
The twelve housekeepers left the building yesterday afternoon without any resistance.
All points out that the nightmares of the neighbors of House No 51 on the street of Balmes have come to an end.
Twelve people volunteered to leave the building, which they held illegally and in which they had organized huge festivals that had led the neighborhood to despair. The clearing took place on a judicial order without police intervention.
After the clearance, the door lock was replaced to avoid a similar situation.
"From now on, access will be checked," the house manager confirmed.
The housekeepers, who had occupied 11 of the 13 apartments of the building - the others were inhabited - took the entire electrical system and part of the water supply. They had painted the walls and left all kinds of garbage, especially doses of alcoholic drinks.
In the three lower floors, huge parties were celebrated, which lasted up to two days and led the tenants to despair.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which also had damage to it.
Her owner, Maria Pantinat, said that her business had fallen by 80% since the start of the house occupation.
The owner of the discotheque pointed out that the housekeepers made her unfair competition, because they sold the drinks to three euros, while they cost 10 euros in the discotheque.
In addition, the owner of the leisure place had been indicated by the neighbors because of a rest disorder, while according to her statement of noise, it was not from the visitors of the disco, but from the housekeepers, and in particular from the guests of the festivals that were organized there, and which, according to the angry neighbors, have been more and more over the last few weeks.
The director of the discotheque said that the harassment had been so great that it agreed with the owner of the building that it would not have to pay rent for the last nine months.
The Guardia Urbana (city police) also confirmed that in the last few weeks it has received more complaints from its neighbours.
The president of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) in the City Council of Barcelona, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had called for the building to be cleared immediately last week and to tackle the problems of civil coexistence and the downfall of the city district.
He explained that before the summer, only one floor of the building had been occupied, but that in the last months, the housekeepers had penetrated into all floors of the building and almost all apartments. In some of them, even theft had occurred.
