The North Stream gas pipeline, which runs on the Baltic Sea and connects the Western Europe directly with Russia, was put into operation.
It is intended to supply gas for an equivalent of 30 million households.
The Russian gas giant Gazprom wanted to commit this event with gloss and Gloria.
